The translator chose a playful, rhythmic repetition that feels natural in French, preserving the whimsical sound and effect of the original rather than its literal form.

= Quotes
*Passage 1 (pg. 373)*
#v(-1em)
#quote()[
  When confronted with such an example, one realizes that it is utterly impossible to make an exact translation.
  Yet even in this pathologically difficult case of translation, there seems to be some rough equivalence obtainable.
  Why ... ?
  The answer is that there is a kind of rough isomorphism, partly global, partly local, between the brains of all the readers of these three poems.
]
#v(-0.8em)
The argument that there exists some rough isomorphism between human brains is one of the central arguments of this chapter.
The example illustrates how this can be if people share symbols and triggering mechanisms even if they come from different backgrounds.

*Passage 2 (pg. 385)*
#v(-1em)
#quote()[
  Our alternative to the soulist explanation---and a disconcerting one it is, too---is to stop at the symbol level and say, "This is it---this is what consciousness _is_. Consciousness is that property of a system that arises whenever there exist symbols in the system which obey triggering patterns ..."
]
#v(-0.8em)
To me this quote is a bit dubious but still central to the chapter.
To think about the self as some inordinately large symbol is not unreasonable but I feel like it still leaves some holes such as what is the level of complexity when it arises and how does this lead to introspection.

= Key Terms / Mappings
- *Centrality:* The quality of being essential or of the greatest importance.
- *Subsystem:* A symbol of sufficiently large complexity which can govern other symbols.
- *Aberrant:* Not conforming to an expected or usual standard
- *Eo Ipso:* by that very act or quality; thereby

= Counter Case or Limitation
I felt like the paragraph discussing memory dumps in the context of understanding programs at a high level did not belong.
It seems to go against the analogy that a program could be understood by analyzing it at a very low level.

